Package: outlieR
Title: Functional Rarity Indices Computations
Version: 0.0.1
Author:
  Matthias Grenié <matthias.grenie@ens-lyon.fr> [aut, cre],
  Pierre Denelle <pierre.denelle@cefe.cnrs.fr> [aut]
Maintainer:
  Matthias Grenié <matthias.grenie@ens-lyon.fr>
Description: Computes functional rarity indices as proposed by Violle et al.
    Various indices can be computed using both regional and local information.
    Most function need a table of sites and species present, plus traits table
    for all the present species. It can also abundance weighted metrics.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.2)
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: true
Imports:
    cluster,
    dplyr (>= 0.4.3),
    moments
URL: https://github.com/Rekyt/outlieR
BugReports: https://github.com/Rekyt/outlieR/issues
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat,
    microbenchmark,
    ggplot2,
    reshape2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
